Instructions to creat! Files 


Okay, I understand! You're looking for a project that combines all the HTML skills you've learned in the past month, like a class assignment with clear instructions. Here's a project that fits that description:

**Project Title:** "My Favorite Things" Website

Project Goal: 
    Create a website showcasing your favorite things, including your favorite song, websites, images, and  audio clips.

**Instructions:**

1. Create a Homepage:**
   Title: "My Favorite Things"
   Include a heading: "Welcome to My Favorite Things!"
    Write a brief paragraph introducing yourself and the purpose of the website.
   Add a navigation menu with links to the following pages:
     - "My Favorite Song"
     - "My Favorite Websites"
     - "My Favorite Images"
     - "My Favorite Audio"

2. **My Favorite Song Page:**
   - Title: "My Favorite Song"
   - Include the song title as a heading (e.g., "Hey There Delilah").
   - Add the song lyrics using the `<pre>` tag to preserve formatting.
   - Include an audio player with the song (if available).
   - Link back to the Homepage.

3. **My Favorite Websites Page:**
   - Title: "My Favorite Websites"
   - Include a heading: "Check out These Awesome Websites!"
   - Add links to your favorite websites (at least 3).
   - Write a brief description for each website.
   - Link back to the Homepage.

4. **My Favorite Images Page:**
   - Title: "My Favorite Images"
   - Include a heading: "My Favorite Images"
   - Add at least 3 images using the `<img>` tag.
   - Provide alt text for each image.
   - Link back to the Homepage.

5. **My Favorite Audio Page:**
   - Title: "My Favorite Audio"
   - Include a heading: "Listen to This!"
   - Add an audio player with your favorite audio clip.
   - Write a brief description of the audio clip.
   - Link back to the Homepage.

**Bonus Challenges:**

- **Add a Contact Page:** Create a form with fields for name, email, and a message. (This form won't be functional yet, but it's good practice.)
- **Use CSS for Styling:** Add a separate CSS file to style your website with different fonts, colors, and layouts.
- **Make it Accessible:** Ensure your website is accessible by using semantic HTML5 tags, ARIA attributes, and proper alt text.

**Grading Rubric:**

- **Functionality:** All links and audio players work correctly.
- **Content:** The website includes all required elements and information.
- **Design:** The website is visually appealing and easy to navigate.
- **Accessibility:** The website is accessible to users with disabilities.

**Submission:**

- Submit your project as a ZIP file containing all HTML files, images, and audio clips.

This project will allow you to practice and demonstrate your HTML skills in a creative and meaningful way. Remember to have fun and personalize it to reflect your unique interests!